examples.en: I pretended to agree with her, just to keep her happy.
The children pretended to be asleep.
The children pretended to be cowboys.
She pretended not to hear, and kept on walking.
He hoped that his pretended interest in classical music would impress the boss.
He pretended to make a phone call.
He pretended to scalp me with his sword.
Her eyes widened in pretended astonishment.
I climbed into bed and pretended to be asleep.
She pretended not to have known the suicide bomber.
He shows a pretended affection for his girlfriend's cat.
The quack pretended to heal patients but never managed to.
He had a big stain on his shirt, but I pretended not to notice.
The people offered to fire at them, if they pretended to go forward.
The little boy pretended to be a comic book hero with supernormal powers.
The father whinnied and reared as his young daughter pretended to ride him.
